'''Jolly''' can be a noun and an adjective.

* a jolly is an event which is perceived to be more enjoyable than useful, and is perhaps a [[freebie]] too
* jolly can mean very, as in "jolly good show"

Usage of the word "jolly" as an adjective is perceived to be [[old fashioned]], conjouring up [[stereotypical]] images of [[crusty]] old [[British India Army]] [[colonel]]s uttering "jolly good show" as they [[pop off]] for [[tiffin]] after the final [[chukka]] of a days [[polo]].

