Jolly is also a name that is found in some name books.  It is listed as an "unusual" name and shares the same meaning as the French name, Jolie.  It is derived from the Old French(OF)word, 
"joli" that means "merriness."

The name is quite popular in Southern India where the French once visited and settled.  It is also used as a result of the British presence.

Currently, Jolly is a unisex name in South India.

Jolly is also commonly used in certain parts of the world where the British have colonized.

In parts of Jamaica, people use the term in expressions.  In Chaucer's day, the word expressed different shades of meaning.

In truth, the word has been around for a very long time.